Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.29,0:22:44.09,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanashii hodo kyō no yūhi kirei da ne\N(Today's sunset is so pretty it's sad)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.25,0:00:20.96,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Hooligan
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.84,0:00:03.31,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Hooligan."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.31,0:00:09.04,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}An outlaw who commits violent and destructive acts in soccer stadiums.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.04,0:00:11.31,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They cause a nuisance, but even so,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.31,0:00:15.31,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}they shouldn't have their life stolen from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:20.96,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today, let's play back a case where a proud, violent hooligan was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.23,0:00:41.56,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If cases were all men,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.56,0:00:43.51,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}then I wonder if the unseen puzzles would be women?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.51,0:00:45.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hooligans are troublesome,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:46.79,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}in the guise of being soccer fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.79,0:00:48.61,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.61,0:00:50.29,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.29,0:00:53.00,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.32,0:02:21.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Tōkyō Spirits vs. Noir Tōkyō!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.74,0:02:24.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The score's still tied at 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.34,0:02:27.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sounds like we may need to go to extra time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.12,0:02:29.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait! The ball was passed to Hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:32.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.20,0:02:34.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.38,0:02:35.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.62,0:02:36.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Three...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.97,0:02:37.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Four!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.67,0:02:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Go for it, Hide! Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.43,0:02:44.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now Hide's one-on-one in front of the goal! Will he shoot like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.11,0:02:46.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But the Noir defenders aren't making it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.49,0:02:48.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They rush him from behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.09,0:02:50.46,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The keeper came out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.46,0:02:51.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The defenders close in too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.73,0:02:54.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Will Hide still shoot?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.19,0:02:55.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, he passed it to the side!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.42,0:02:56.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And ahead of the ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.82,0:02:58.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's Naoki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:04.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:11.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Naoki's explosive heading shot breaks the tie!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.67,0:03:17.43,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And that's the match's final whistle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.43,0:03:22.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}During injury time in the second half, with Naoki's goal, the Tōkyō Spirits defeated Noir Tōkyō,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.29,0:03:25.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and have won the Tōkyō Derby...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:01.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,It's awesome, Hide dribbled through four players!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:02.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:06.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,And everybody on the main stand was excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:09.13,Dialogue,,0001,0001,0020,,Dodging from right to left like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.13,0:04:11.26,Dialogue,,0001,0001,0020,,he looked like Baggio!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.26,0:04:13.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,Naoki was pretty awesome, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:15.16,Dialogue,,0001,0001,0020,,After all, he'd already jumped
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.16,0:04:16.70,Dialogue,,0001,0001,0020,,even before Hide passed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.70,0:04:17.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,Hide and Naoki:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.97,0:04:20.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,The perfect revival of the golden combo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.95,0:04:22.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,But I had no idea
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.17,0:04:24.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,the Spirits were gonna have such a hard time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.97,0:04:29.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,I was afraid we'd go to extra time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:32.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,Couldn't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.75,0:04:36.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,Noir Tōkyō's best players are injured,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:37.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,and since the center-forward Higo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.92,0:04:39.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,signed up for Big Ōsaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:41.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,they're lacking in powerful players.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.70,0:04:45.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They toughened up their defense from the start, trying for a draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.96,0:04:48.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of Higo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:53.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The other match between Noir and Big Ōsaka was pretty awesome too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.52,0:04:58.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... but they booed Higo every time he got the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.48,0:05:02.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did their supporters boo him too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.31,0:05:03.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.01,0:05:09.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, there's no place for traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.91,0:05:10.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.89,0:05:12.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.89,0:05:16.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's hated by both friend and foe alike, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:20.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Noir and Big have been rivals for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.22,0:05:26.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Big supporters can't cheer honestly for a forward who they've seen as an enemy until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.38,0:05:30.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, even after five matches, Higo still hasn't scored a goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.40,0:05:35.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it, I remember seeing Higo in a sports newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.61,0:05:38.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Is he going to Spain?", it said.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.31,0:05:41.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it was on the sports news too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.61,0:05:47.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They said he signed up with Big to increase the price of his contract when he went to Spain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:48.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an awful guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.74,0:05:51.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.18,0:05:53.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a rumour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.24,0:05:57.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if the rumour is right, then he'll probably be much better off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.70,0:06:05.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's his chance to forget everything and escape to a place where the booing won't reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.88,0:06:10.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.16,0:06:17.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:19.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think there's a Big match today, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:23.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they'll broadcast it on Nichiuri TV at 5 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.46,0:06:28.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! The match's started!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.42,0:06:30.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.02,0:06:37.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There is tremendous booing. The source is, of course, Ryūsuke Higo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.64,0:06:41.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. Serves him right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:45.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what happens when you betray us at Noir Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.15,0:06:51.26,Signs,,0000,0000,0020,,Kadotake Akano (48)\NNoir Tōkyō Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:51.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,Once you've fallen to Hell, you'll never get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.58,0:06:55.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:58.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where have I seen that guy before...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.54,0:07:02.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw him in the news on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.48,0:07:06.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He tends to get drunk on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:11.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,fires off smoke rockets at the field, and starts big fights. I think his name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.03,0:07:12.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kadotake Akano.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.76,0:07:15.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a staunch supporter of Noir Tōkyō,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.54,0:07:18.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a stupid old man who's proud to be a hooligan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.67,0:07:24.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's even been blacklisted, and isn't allowed entrance in many stadiums.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.96,0:07:26.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's a "hooligan"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.93,0:07:32.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Obnoxious supporters in Europe who start fights during matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.68,0:07:37.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That old guy even has a "Tōkyō Hooligan" home page.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.10,0:07:43.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He even keeps a diary saying things like what he's done to other supporters on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:46.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I guess he can't do much if they won't let him in the stadiums.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.73,0:07:52.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.92,0:07:56.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of homepages, did you check {\i1}that{\i0} one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.90,0:08:00.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, the one I asked you to look into the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.21,0:08:04.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That American movie star's homepage, Chris Vineyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:07.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Like you told me to, Shin'ichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.43,0:08:11.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went into the chat and asked fans some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.09,0:08:11.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.97,0:08:14.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't learn much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.87,0:08:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her mother, Sharon Vineyard, was quite famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:23.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the daughter Chris's private life is covered by a veil of mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.94,0:08:27.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only time she appeared in front of the media, other than for photos,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:30.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was that day, a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.64,0:08:31.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"That" day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.90,0:08:35.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her mother Sharon's funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.05,0:08:38.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They even aired stuff about it on the Japanese news, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.69,0:08:40.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.25,0:08:44.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently a particularly unscrupulous reporter snuck into the funeral,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.31,0:08:47.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and kept bugging her with questions like...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.59,0:08:49.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"What school did you go to?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:51.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Did you really not get along with your mother?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.50,0:08:53.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Who's your real father?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:55.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Do you have a boyfriend? Did he come with you to the funeral?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.18,0:09:01.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she made no comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.40,0:09:03.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And frustrated at her attitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.69,0:09:07.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a reporter asked "Are you trying to hide something?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.41,0:09:14.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She then turned her back to her mother's coffin, and with a slight smile on her face she flatly answered...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.64,0:09:18.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"A secret makes a woman woman."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.88,0:09:23.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A secret is what makes a woman a woman, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.12,0:09:25.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.12,0:09:30.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Chris Vineyard really with the men in black?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:31.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.54,0:09:35.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any proof yet. But if it's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.05,0:09:37.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happens if it's true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.51,0:09:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd be a tough enemy to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:45.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tough?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.06,0:09:46.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.98,0:09:49.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't happen to be hiding something from me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.89,0:09:57.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, because she's a good actress, it'd be hard to corner her with deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:10:01.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, shouldn't we be on the train home by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.71,0:10:03.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.24,0:10:06.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys! We're going home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.26,0:10:08.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.08,0:10:09.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just getting good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.58,0:10:11.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.31,0:10:13.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.06,0:10:14.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.52,0:10:15.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:17.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.84,0:10:21.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, we're off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:38.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this train?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.37,0:10:41.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of fans of the Spirits and Noir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:45.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I said we should take the next train.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.69,0:10:48.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you were in a hurry to get home...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.92,0:10:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to watch the Big match in my TV at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.27,0:10:55.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.45,0:10:58.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurts, ya moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.48,0:11:01.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just 'cause ya won don't mean ya get to push people around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.69,0:11:05.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it, the train's full...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.22,0:11:08.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That old guy's on the same train as us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.13,0:11:09.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.42,0:11:12.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't bring attention to ourselves, he'll probably leave us alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.62,0:11:15.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,True, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.63,0:11:21.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.16,0:11:23.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how's the match?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.45,0:11:25.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.32,0:11:29.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still 0-0, and we're entering the first half's injury time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.66,0:11:33.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And is Big's number 9 still on the field?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:36.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you mean Higo, he's still out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:41.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the booing is so loud, that his teammates hesitate to pass to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.25,0:11:43.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.59,0:11:46.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.04,0:11:50.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If something happens in the match, let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.97,0:11:53.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.50,0:12:04.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.27,0:12:09.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Haido, Haido...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.44,0:12:12.87,Thoughts,,0001,0001,0000,,{\be10}Passengers transferring to the Haido subway line change here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.93,0:12:29.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One stab to the stomach with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:31.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what happened, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.73,0:12:34.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc! Get an ambulance and the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.82,0:12:35.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.74,0:12:38.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Can I make it in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:40.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! {anyone feels like subbing it literally as 'station master{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:43.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move this train!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.34,0:12:44.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A man's been stabbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.92,0:12:46.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:50.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, please call the ticket control barriers connected to this platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.88,0:12:56.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and ask them to check all the tickets from Tōkyō Spirits and Noir Tōkyō supporters trying to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:13:00.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Supporters? Tickets?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:06.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Stop anyone who has a ticket bought before 5 PM from leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.02,0:13:08.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.17,0:13:13.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just do it! If you don't, the killer might get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.39,0:13:22.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim is Kadotake Akano, 48.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.11,0:13:26.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder weapon was a knife with a 15 cm blade, found at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.11,0:13:26.03,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,(6 inch)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.93,0:13:30.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time of the murder, there were a lot of passengers on the train,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.61,0:13:33.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but no witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.89,0:13:36.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't I seen this man somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:39.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.60,0:13:40.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.99,0:13:44.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This man was a rather rude supporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.51,0:13:47.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and appeared often on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:49.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.81,0:13:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The knife's handle and scabbard both have a rather unusual design.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.70,0:13:55.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can track its purchase...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.52,0:13:58.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,About that, I've already asked about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:04.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that knife is apparently rare and foreign. It's also not sold in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.23,0:14:08.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It will take a long time to find where it could've been purchased.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:10.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:14.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if a person was stabbed in a train,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.32,0:14:16.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,how come nobody saw it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.53,0:14:17.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.12,0:14:21.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the train was packed full.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.73,0:14:23.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.25,0:14:28.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When we got to the station, everyone rushed out, and that man collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.49,0:14:32.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was when we noticed someone had been stabbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:34.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.29,0:14:37.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys again!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.64,0:14:40.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, did you see anyone suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.85,0:14:44.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't remember. Everybody was dressed the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:46.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dressed the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.48,0:14:49.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A soccer match just ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.23,0:14:52.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the train was full of supporters from the two teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.82,0:14:55.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.20,0:14:58.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a good chance the killer left the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.66,0:15:01.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or switched to another train.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.25,0:15:03.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:08.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I explained to three passengers what happened, and asked them to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.73,0:15:11.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And how did you select those three passengers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.70,0:15:17.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was really just following what this kid told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.00,0:15:18.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And "this kid..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.72,0:15:19.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.27,0:15:23.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:24.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.65,0:15:27.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why those three?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.22,0:15:28.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.94,0:15:34.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't just decide to stab someone on a train, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.86,0:15:36.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.41,0:15:42.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer must've known Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was going to travel in this train filled with supporters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.50,0:15:46.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he must've stabbed Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with the knife just before arriving at this station,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.77,0:15:52.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where he knew a lot of people would rush out, then mixed in with the passengers to try and escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:56.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So basically, it's a premeditated murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.43,0:15:57.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.30,0:16:04.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I asked the supervisor to not let anyone dressed like either of the teams leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.90,0:16:07.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why supporters?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.36,0:16:11.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the train was filled with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.47,0:16:14.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't stand out much if you were dressed as one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:19.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then only three supporters tried to leave the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:22.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there were around fifty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.71,0:16:25.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the numbers don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:27.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.99,0:16:29.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The ticket?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.17,0:16:36.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To stab Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the killer had to follow him and get on the same train, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.06,0:16:40.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, the killer had to buy the return ticket in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.10,0:16:45.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he tried to buy a ticket after the match, the line would be crowded with supporters,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.57,0:16:49.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and if he tried to buy a ticket then, he would've lost Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.32,0:16:51.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The match ended at 5 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.97,0:17:01.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, only three people had a ticket marked before 5 PM and tried to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.01,0:17:09.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if the killer changed clothes before leaving the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.07,0:17:13.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or transferred to the train on the opposite platform without trying to leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:15.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not very likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.90,0:17:18.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd look pretty suspicious if he changed clothes on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.61,0:17:21.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this station's toilet is outside the ticket control barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:28.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There wouldn't be a lot of supporters on another platform, so someone could remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:33.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,While waiting for the train, the police could've caught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.11,0:17:34.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The safest way would be:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.88,0:17:37.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the station with all the supporters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.84,0:17:41.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,change clothes in the toilet, and escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.21,0:17:47.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of passengers get off at Haido Station to transfer onto the subway, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.58,0:17:49.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:51.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.72,0:17:54.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I always end up wondering this but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.30,0:17:57.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...just how are you so intelligent?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:02.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You deduced all of this the instant you saw the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.83,0:18:05.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and gave the supervisor instructions, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.11,0:18:07.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.13,0:18:09.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.52,0:18:11.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.81,0:18:15.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just following the doctor's instructions!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:17.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It was you, Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.54,0:18:19.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:22.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.41,0:18:25.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was just following my instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.59,0:18:29.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way a kid could deduce a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.56,0:18:33.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is totally embarrassing...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:35.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And have you figured out who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.48,0:18:38.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume you at least have some idea, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.60,0:18:40.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.40,0:18:47.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, what did I tell Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} to do after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.31,0:18:48.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.73,0:18:50.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh right, doc,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:54.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you said you'd listen to them after the police arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.69,0:18:57.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The three people who the supervisor retained, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.36,0:19:03.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.87,0:19:06.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're treating us like criminals just because we bought a ticket at a certain time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.95,0:19:11.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought the return ticket ahead of time so I could avoid the crowds later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.76,0:19:13.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Same.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.07,0:19:14.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:19.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But all three of you went on a train full of supporters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.67,0:19:26.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you bought a ticket ahead of time, why didn't you get on a train before it got crowded?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.33,0:19:27.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.45,0:19:34.34,Signs,,0000,0000,0020,,Hasue Kira (24)\NNoir Tōkyō Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.89,0:19:29.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,After the match,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.74,0:19:33.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,I got into an argument with a Spirits supporter, {next to me}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.57,0:19:35.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,and ended up being late to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.87,0:19:42.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the main stand where the Spirits and Noir supporters were grouped together!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.36,0:19:47.15,Dialogue,,0001,0001,0020,,I got a phone call from work before the end of the match,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.72,0:19:48.60,Signs,,0001,0001,0020,,Mitsuaki Funato (33)\NTōkyō Spirits Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.15,0:19:49.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,since they found out I was skipping work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:54.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They yelled at me a lot, so I couldn't go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.00,0:19:57.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, I even missed the two wingers' winning goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.71,0:20:03.70,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Etsutoshi Ōba (29)\NNoir Tōkyō Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.71,0:20:00.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,Even though the match had ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.79,0:20:02.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,I was in such shock I couldn't even stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:06.04,Dialogue,,0001,0001,0020,,When Hide dribbled past the defenders and approached,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.04,0:20:08.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,and Naoki scored the goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:10.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0020,,I just went blank...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:15.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And which train car were you on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:17.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember that kind of stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.65,0:20:21.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure all three of them were on a crowded car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.51,0:20:23.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.49,0:20:28.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On your right elbow, there's a mark from the ring on your left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.30,0:20:32.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you carried your bag on your right shoulder for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.70,0:20:35.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and held the bag shut with your left hand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.31,0:20:43.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The watch mark on the long-haired guy's right arm is proof he had his arms crossed a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.16,0:20:47.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the guy with the glasses has marks on his palms,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.71,0:20:51.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from holding a bag really hard with both hands, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.84,0:20:58.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only time you'd pose like that and not hold onto the straps would be on a crowded train.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.22,0:21:04.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And since the train was already full when we arrived, you couldn't find a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.15,0:21:07.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that all correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.08,0:21:08.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.12,0:21:11.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They say there's a lot of thefts on crowded trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.23,0:21:15.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to be mistaken for a pervert if I didn't keep my arms crossed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.69,0:21:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! It's just like the doc said!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.99,0:21:27.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we know you were in a crowded car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.28,0:21:33.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like it if you could remember what car you were on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.31,0:21:37.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then if you would please come with me to the car where the crime took place...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.57,0:21:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta get back to the company...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.56,0:21:43.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, what is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.32,0:21:44.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(50,50)}Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.11,0:21:47.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(50,50)}Why is that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.61,0:22:10.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(100,100)}We have three suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.98,0:22:17.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(100,100)}The only thing we know for sure is that they all rode in a packed train car.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.70,0:22:22.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(100,100)}But that's not enough to conclude anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.52,0:22:26.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(100,100)}There's gotta be something... There's gotta be something more!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.24,0:22:31.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(100,100)}Some other clue to solve the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.21,0:24:03.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Higo was knocked down!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.08,0:24:08.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Listen to the audience's cheering.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.55,0:24:15.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Has Higo been forsaken by all who supported him? Is there no field in Japan where Higo can play?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.31,0:24:17.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.35,0:24:19.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\fad(0,200)}If I recall correctly, today's Tōkyō Derby was...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.23,0:24:24.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As I thought...
